      <div type="translation" n="B55">
        <div type="textpart" n="B55K1">
          <ab n="B55K1V1" corresp="#Bel.1.1.P827.I1">
            <ab n="B55K1V1" corresp="#Bel.1.1.P827.I1"> And King Astyages was added beside his
              fathers and Cyrus the Persian received his kingdom.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V2" corresp="Bel.1.2.P827.I1"> And Daniel was a companion of the king and
              was esteemed above all his friends.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V3" corresp="Bel.1.3.P827.I1"> And there was an idol to the Babylonians
              called Bel, and every day into him consumed twelve artaba<anchor n="1" xml:id="B55K1V3-note-1"/> fine wheaten flour and
              forty sheep and six measures of wine.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V4" corresp="Bel.1.4.P828.I1"> And the king worshipped it. And every day
              Daniel fell down making obeisance to God, but he made obeisance to his God. And he
              said to the king he would not make obeisance to Bel.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V5" corresp="Bel.1.5.P828.I1"> And he said, "That I worship not an idol made
              by human hands, but the living God builder of heaven and earth, and lord of all flesh
              things.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V6" corresp="Bel.1.6.P828.I1"> And the king said to him, "Does it not seem
              to you Bel is a living god, not see or much as eat and drink according to every
              day?</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V7" corresp="Bel.1.7.P828.I1"> And Daniel laughing said, "Do not be led
              astray, king, for it is clay from within indeed, from without but copper, and has
              never ate.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V8" corresp="Bel.1.8.P828.I1"> And the king, being angered, summoned his
              priests and said to them, "If none says to me who devours this spent expenditure, you
              will die,</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V9" corresp="Bel.1.9.P828.I1"> but if you bring to light Bel devours it,
              Daniel will die, he that blasphemes Bel." And Daniel said to the king, "Begin
              according to what you say."</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V10" corresp="Bel.1.10.P828.I1"> And seventy priests of Bel go outside with
              their wives and children, and the king goes with Daniel, stranger of Bel.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V11" corresp="Bel.1.11.P829.I1"> And the priests of Bel say, "Look! We run
              out, but you, O king, set before the food and mingle wine, closing the door and
              sealing it with your ring!</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V12" corresp="Bel.1.12.P829.I1"> And if coming early in the day you may not
              find all eaten up by Bel, we die, or Daniel the deceiver against us.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V13" corresp="Bel.1.13.P829.I1"> And they despised, because they had hidden
              under the table an entrance, and would enter through it altogether and eat.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V14" corresp="Bel.1.14.P829.I1"> And it happened as they came out that they,
              and the king put them beside the food to Bel. And Daniel ordered his servants and they
              carried ashes, and shook them across the temple in the presence of only the king, and
              going out shut the door and sealed it in by the ring of the king, and went away.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V15" corresp="Bel.1.15.P829.I1"> But the priests and their wives and
              children went at night according to their habit, and ate up all and drank.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V16" corresp="Bel.1.16.P829.I1"> And early in the morning the king awoke,
              and Daniel with him.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V17" corresp="Bel.1.17.P829.I1"> And they said, "Safe seals, Daniel?" and he
              said, "Safe, king."</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V18" corresp="Bel.1.18.P829.I1"> And they began at once to open the door,
              the king looking upon the table shouted in a loud voice, "You are great, Bel, and it
              is not treachery beside nor into you."</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V19" corresp="Bel.1.19.P830.I1"> And Daniel laughed, and taking possesion of
              himself the king did not go into him, and he said, "Look indeed at the ground, and
              know whose footprints these are!</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V20" corresp="Bel.1.20.P830.I1"> And the king said, "I see the footsteps of
              the men and the women and the children." </ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V21" corresp="Bel.1.21.P830.I1"> And the king was growing angry then
              collected the priests and the wives and children of them, and brought to light the
              door hidden by them through which they would enter and consume the food upon the
              table.</ab>
            <ab n="B55K1V22" corresp="Bel.1.22.P830.I1"> And the king killed them, and gave up Bel
              to Daniel, and overturned him and his temple.</ab>
            <note corresp="B54K1V3-note-1">It took a bit of research, but it turns out an "artaba" is itself a unit of measurement</note>
          </ab>
